ADVANCE OFFERING OF THE GREAT

1979 RED BORDEAUX

Is 1979 a great year? How does it compare to the ’78s, ’75s and 61s? We asked Philippe Cottin, Managing Director of Chateau Mouton-Rothschild and he re- sponded “:..1979 does not have the intensity or high tannin that marks the ‘45s, ’6ls and ’75s, but it compensates with an abundance of fruit, soft charm and a promise of superb development ahead. It is in the style of the outstanding 1959 vintage and in my book—it is a winner!”

Our in-depth Spring visit to Bordeaux confirmed this opinion. The excellence of the year now recognized by the wine drinkers of the world has forced the prices upward 30% on the Bordeaux market in a short span of 4 months. The process will continue. Now is the time to buy. Order now—delivery during 1982.
